## TL;DR: What Every 2ct Cushion Buyer Must Know First

The 2 carat cushion cut diamond ring is the most requested size in the cushion category — large enough to read dramatically on the hand, small enough that quality grades still matter. At 2ct, the cushion's softened corners and crushed ice brilliance look their best, and the face-up size (~8mm square) creates visible impact without the finger-dwarfing effect of a 3ct.

**Contrarian Truth — The Pillow Premium:** Most buyers enter the cushion market expecting it to be cheaper than round — it is not. At 2ct in GIA F-VVS2 Ideal quality, the natural cushion is $13,679 from Blue Nile. The equivalent 2ct round in the same quality tier runs 10–20% higher, but the cushion commands 8–15% more than a princess cut at the same grade. Buyers who switch from princess to cushion mid-search are surprised to pay more, not less.

**Live price snapshot (Blue Nile {{year}}):**
- Lab 2ct IGI D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Natural 2ct GIA F-VVS2 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$13,679](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29359194?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- Natural 2ct GIA G-VVS2 Ideal Cushion Modified: **[$16,584](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28768883?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**→ The best entry point** for lab buyers is the [IGI 2ct D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified at $2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — D colour (top), VVS1 (genuinely invisible inclusions), Ideal cut, crushed ice modified brilliant. For natural buyers with a strong quality preference, the [GIA 2ct F-VVS2 Ideal at $13,679](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29359194?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the benchmark.

