## What Is a 2 Carat Cushion Cut Diamond Ring?

A 2 carat cushion cut diamond ring combines a 2ct cushion-shaped diamond — approximately 8mm × 8mm face-up in standard square proportions — with an engagement ring setting. The cushion cut's softened corners, rounded edges, and pillow-like outline distinguish it from the hard-cornered princess cut and the circular round brilliant. At 2ct, the cushion reads as a genuinely substantial stone on the hand: larger than most people wear day-to-day, unmistakable in social settings.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The [2 carat cushion cut diamond ring](/cushion-cut-diamond) represents the ideal size entry point for buyers who want the cushion's distinctive character at full visual impact. Below 1.5ct, the cushion's soft outline reads as delicate rather than dramatic. Above 2.5ct, most buyers begin encountering setting challenges and significant natural diamond price escalation. At exactly 2ct, the cushion's proportions, the availability of quality diamonds at multiple price points, and the variety of compatible settings all converge.

What separates excellent 2ct cushion purchases from average ones: understanding The Pillow Premium (why cushions cost more than princess at 2ct) and The Modified Brilliant Split (why two 2ct cushions at the same price can look completely different). Both concepts are covered below.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

