## The Pillow Premium

The Pillow Premium is the price difference between a 2ct cushion cut diamond and a 2ct princess cut diamond of equivalent quality — and it runs in the direction most buyers do not expect. Cushions are more expensive than princess at 2ct, not cheaper.

[![Cushion cut diamond engagement ring in rose gold solitaire with pavé band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/502250/502250_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

The structural reason for The Pillow Premium: cutting a cushion requires removing more diamond rough than cutting a princess from the same octahedral crystal. The princess cut is essentially a square section of the rough with minimal waste; the cushion requires rounding the corners and shaping the pavilion, which wastes material. At 2ct finished weight, a cushion started from a larger piece of rough than a princess of identical weight.

The demand reason: cushion cuts have gained market share consistently for fifteen years as buyers moved away from the sharp-cornered princess in favour of softer, more vintage-looking shapes. Higher demand at 2ct — a sweet-spot size for cushion buyers — has pushed prices up relative to princess.

**What The Pillow Premium means for buyers.** If you are comparing a 2ct GIA G-VS1 cushion to a 2ct GIA G-VS1 princess, expect the cushion to cost 8–15% more. At $13,679 for a 2ct cushion GIA F-VVS2, the equivalent princess at the same grade would typically be $11,500–$12,000. The premium is real and consistent across quality grades.

**When The Pillow Premium disappears.** In the lab grown market, The Pillow Premium largely disappears. Lab cushion and lab princess production are both abundant, and the price differential between cut styles at equal lab quality grades has compressed. A 2ct lab cushion D-VVS1 at $2,606 and a 2ct lab princess D-VVS1 are within a few hundred dollars of each other. The Pillow Premium is primarily a natural diamond phenomenon.

**Is The Pillow Premium worth it?** Yes, for buyers who specifically want the cushion's visual character — the softened corners, the pillow outline, the crushed ice sparkle pattern of the modified brilliant. No, for buyers who chose cushion primarily because they assumed it would be cheaper than round and cheaper than princess. If price is the primary driver, princess offers more diamond per dollar at 2ct. If aesthetics are the primary driver, the cushion's distinctive character justifies the premium.

