## The Modified Brilliant Split

The Modified Brilliant Split is the most important technical concept for any cushion buyer at 2ct — and the one most likely to cause regret if ignored.

[![Cushion cut diamond solitaire engagement ring white gold pavé band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/501590/501590_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box5_001_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Blue Nile's cushion inventory — both natural and lab — contains two visually distinct sub-types:

**Cushion Modified Brilliant.** Additional pavilion facets create a "crushed ice" effect: dense, uniform, fine sparkle across the entire face-up surface. GIA and IGI certificates describe this sub-type as "Cushion Modified Brilliant." This is the dominant sub-type in BN's inventory. At 2ct (approximately 8mm face-up), the crushed ice pattern is clearly visible and creates a bright, photogenic stone that reads well in every lighting environment.

**Cushion Brilliant.** Fewer, larger pavilion facets create a pattern of distinct, larger flashes with visible facet boundaries. GIA and IGI describe this as "Cushion Brilliant." The cushion brilliant at 2ct shows more fire — colour dispersion visible as rainbow flashes at the facet boundaries — and creates a warmer, more traditional diamond look. It resembles a [old mine cushion cut](/old-mine-cushion-cut-diamond) more closely in character than the modified brilliant does.

At 2ct, both sub-types are available at essentially the same price points. The critical difference is visible face-up: the modified brilliant produces a uniform carpet of small light reflections; the cushion brilliant produces larger, more widely spaced flashes with dark intervals between them.

**How to choose at 2ct.** For pavé, halo, and most modern settings where the stone will be viewed from directly above: modified brilliant. For buyers seeking a warmer, character-driven stone with estate or vintage aesthetic: cushion brilliant. For buyers purchasing primarily for photography (Instagram, professional portraits): modified brilliant photographs significantly more dramatically. Request the 360° HD video from BN for every stone you consider — the facet pattern difference is immediately visible in motion.

For the full technical breakdown of this concept, see the [lab grown cushion cut diamond guide](/lab-grown-cushion-cut-diamond) where both sub-types are documented with live pricing at 2ct.

