## 2ct Cushion Cut Engagement Ring Settings

Choosing the right setting for a 2ct cushion cut engagement ring is the second major decision after stone selection. The 2ct cushion's square-ish proportions (typically 7.8–8.3mm face-up) are well served by a range of settings, but not all settings suit the cushion equally.

[![Cushion cut diamond halo engagement ring white gold four-prong](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/501410/501410_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box5_003_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**Halo setting.** The halo is the most popular setting for a 2ct cushion because it amplifies the apparent size of the center stone. A cushion halo ring — a ring of melee diamonds surrounding the cushion center — adds approximately 0.5mm to the visual perimeter of the stone on each side, creating a face-up appearance closer to a 2.5ct. For a 2ct lab cushion at $2,606, a well-executed halo setting from Blue Nile or a local jeweller adds $500–$1,200 and creates a total ring that reads significantly more expensive than its actual cost. For complete halo analysis, see the [cushion cut engagement ring guide](/cushion-cut-diamond-engagement-ring).

**Solitaire setting.** A 2ct cushion in a clean four-prong solitaire allows the stone's modified brilliant sparkle pattern to dominate without competition. The solitaire setting is the correct choice for buyers who specifically selected the stone for its visual properties and want nothing to distract from them. The cushion's softened corners are well served by four prongs positioned at the corners — the prongs follow the stone's outline naturally.

[![Cushion cut diamond pavé engagement ring white gold four-prong flat lay](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/502820/502820_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box5_001_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**Pavé setting.** A pavé band with a 2ct cushion center creates a continuous sparkle surface from the shank to the center stone. The modified brilliant's crushed ice pattern and the pavé band's micro-diamonds both create fine, dense sparkle — they work together rather than competing. The pavé shank also creates a visual narrowing effect that makes the 2ct cushion appear proportionally larger by contrast.

**Split shank setting.** The split shank setting — where the band divides into two strands approaching the center stone — creates a framing effect that emphasises the cushion's square proportions. For a 2ct cushion, the split shank adds visual width to the overall ring presentation. It is the setting style most likely to attract comment from bystanders who notice the ring structure independent of the stone.

[![Cushion cut diamond split shank engagement ring yellow gold](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioSuperImposeBox/Rings/502620/502620_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box3_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**Vintage and milgrain settings.** The cushion's historical origins — it descends from the [old mine cut](/old-mine-cushion-cut-diamond) of the 19th century — make it the natural partner for milgrain, filigree, and vintage-style settings. A 2ct cushion modified brilliant in a vintage milgrain setting creates a ring that reads as an heirloom piece regardless of whether the stone is natural or lab grown. The setting's historical character and the cushion's period-appropriate outline reinforce each other.

[![Cushion cut diamond vintage milgrain engagement ring white gold](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/502482/502482_M1_CSH_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box8_003_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?ShapeID=Cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

