## 2ct Cushion Cut Diamond Ring: Rose Gold

Rose gold is the second most requested metal for 2ct cushion rings after white gold, and it is particularly well-matched to the cushion cut's visual character. The warm pink tone of rose gold creates a contrast with the cool white brilliance of a D-F colour cushion modified brilliant that makes both the stone and the metal appear more vivid.

For a 2ct cushion in rose gold, the ideal colour grade is F-G. In rose gold, the warm metal reflects into the pavilion of the stone and adds a slight warmth regardless of colour grade. Paying the D-E colour premium for a 2ct cushion in rose gold is spending $1,000–$2,000 more for a colour upgrade that the setting partially negates. F colour in rose gold is visually equivalent to D in white gold from a body colour standpoint.

The [2ct IGI D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion Modified at $2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) set in a rose gold solitaire or pavé shank is an outstanding combination — the D colour premium is included in the lab stone price rather than being an additional spend, and the setting cost in rose gold from Blue Nile is comparable to white gold.

